'''Central Bloc''' ({{Lang-pt|Bloco Central}}) is the name given in [[Portugal]] to the [[grand coalition]] of the [[Socialist Party (Portugal)|Socialist Party]] and the [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|Social Democratic Party]] which ruled from 1983 to 1985, and to any potential coalition between those two parties.

